@AN-535  Since you've config visualMap. In series that controlled by visualMap, if a data item needs to escape from controlled by visualMap, you can set like this:
```
data: [{
       name: 'ÊãâËê®',
       visualMap: false,
       value: geoCoordMap['ÊãâËê®'].concat([100]),
}],
```

refer to: https://www.echartsjs.com/en/option.html#visualMap

@nieyt do you mean: https://www.echartsjs.com/examples/en/editor.html?c=doc-example/pie-highlight

you can highlight one item by dispatching 'highlight' action.
pls refer to: https://www.echartsjs.com/en/tutorial.html#Events%20and%20Actions%20in%20ECharts

@akvaliya  I believe Ovilia has given quite straightforward answer.
```
title: {
        text: `${data[0].name} count: ${data[0].value}`,
        left: 'center',
        top: 'center',
        textStyle: {
            color: '#ccc'
        }
    },

```

try demo : https://gallery.echartsjs.com/editor.html?c=xY55c6SEV&v=5

@saojun1024  I am not sure how you make line trail, maybe you use customized symbol in effectLine layer.
[An enhancement](https://github.com/apache/incubator-echarts/pull/11893) in effect line has been included in master branch, which can be tested in next release. you guys can have a try, thanks.
hence close the issue, if any issue still exist, feel free to reopen it.

